      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/32/2/67/405",
      "text": [
        "فَالْعَاكِفُ: الْمُقيِمُ بِهِ، وَالْبَادِي: الَّذِي يَحُجُّ إِلَيْهِ مِنْ غَيْرِ أَهْلِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-ali-raza": [
          "“al-‘ākif” (the dweller) here means he who is living there while “al-bādī” (the stranger) means he who is not among the people of Mecca, comes for ḥajj from outside."
        ]
      }
    }
  },
